          {
            "commit": "edc16c071f8c025b94bd72a26e857bbf7cf79587",
            "subject": "LU-2550 osc: set resend count properly"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "niu@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-02-19 02:05:04.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "niu@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-02-19 02:05:04.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-2824 mds: don't deactivate OSC if osc_create returns -EBUSY",
        "message": "LU-2824 mds: don't deactivate OSC if osc_create returns -EBUSY\n\nDuring MDS<->OST orphan recovery, osc_create() will likely return\n-EBUSY while OSCC_FLAG_SYNC_IN_PROGRESS flag is still set\ndue to slow ll_mdt service thread. The __mds_lov_synchronize() will\nthen deactivate the OSC, which will cause mds_create_objects() get\n-EIO error.\n\nThis patch fixes the above issue by checking the return value of\nmds_lov_clear_orphans(). If it's -EBUSY, then do not mark the\nOSC as inactive.\n\nTest-Parameters: envdefinitions=DURATION=14400 clientdistro=el5 serverdistro=el5 clientarch=x86_64 serverarch=x86_64 clientcount=4 osscount=2 mdscount=2 austeroptions=-R failover=true useiscsi=true testlist=recovery-mds-scale\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I7b3376e3b6087dd35c5f0e33e98b1e538ba711fc\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
